    <item>
      <title>Re: How to Fix EQ PvP - Address the real issue</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=899#M899</link>
      <description>Rytan, I honestly doubt a PvP ranking system will work. Maybe only if you scale down you killing the same person making you receive points like only once a week and/or if the helping groupmembers (healer debuffer) receive points either. The bounty system is a not a bad idea though, but dunno how it works when implemented, prolly only if you can only place one offer a time and when the victim is killed the offer is canceled. Keep in mind that its all about fun in PvP and harrassing and exploiting are harming the servers more then a bounty or point system will aid them IMHO - so please only implement those features if they bring fun not frustration.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Every spell should have a minimum chance to land (lets say 10-20%) and besides that there should be an exponential resist system valuing the first 100 resist more then the next 100 and so on to make gear still worthwile but not overpowering. Decreasing the amount of time "critical" spells like snare stick or having a chance to break them when hit is a good idea.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Balance in PvP can never be achieved IMHO but a stone / paper system where classes have the ability to kill one class easier could help some with that issue. Balancing also means to keep in mind that there is not only outdoors but also indoors where the melees have the upper hand usually. Wouldnt mind some Magic immunity skills in PvP for pure melees as tradeoff for lacking spells and / or a nasty range weapon disc that stuns the opponent for some time to enable the pure melee to actually kill someone.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Insta gate discs are a problem in PvP and I d really like to see Spirit of Cheetah be the fastest run speed in game since it has only a few seconds duration. Wiz can step anyways.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bards and Insta kills and fastheals are a problem, too so giving bards more offensive power while making them vulnerable to runs speed decrease and less annoying (mez / drain) same as making Dru Shm Clr Pal MR Pr Dr spells less resisted if tuning down healing on people hit in PvP "who are in pvp mode".&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;PoT and a few other zones being PvP enabled sounds nice - but PoK should be unchanged IMHO.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Would there be a chance to implement a "just zoned" flag that prevents you from zoning a few seconds so zone dancing wouldnt be an issue anymore or is this too much effort to code?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Anyways its good to see finally some constructive cooperation on implementing changes on the PvP servers.&lt;br&gt;As most people already noticed there are at least two fractions of PvP players - some are hardcore and some are blue. Luckily there are several server setups so both fractions will hopefully find their home in the end.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Not to forget that a lot of bored players on the "blue" servers could be interested into "blue" PvP servers (or lets say low grief factor servers) with that changes and the proper promotion. The positive things on a PvP server is that reputation, friends, gear really matter her and that you have additional options while playing EQ. My dream was always a Light vs Dark server (maybe including Neutrals ie Humans) where you can change factions via Quests and take faction hits for kills. This server would need an ongoing storyline and a lot of events like fights for cities and wars. The server would have an online chronicle where the players are the figures of the chronicle developing via the events and you could read that story like an Dragonlance book with screen shots. Ok prolly too much work and support staff needed but maybe someday? ;)</description>
