      <title>Re: New to PvP and looking for advice</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=489#M489</link>
      <description>Well, if you are looking for "hardcore" PvP and are willing to accept that you might get harrased and have some frustration from time to time you should try out Rallos or even Sullon. If you just want to have some occasional PvP on servers that have player made rules against harassing you should try Vz Tz. Even though in lower levels those rules like "loot and scoot" "no corpsecamping" "no engaging when in a fight (not including running into mobs on purpose)" etc etc. are not known by every player or sometimes misinterpreted or not obeyed. But once in higher levels your reputation as griefer will usually hinder you to get into a high lvl guild and once in range of the high level guilds without friends and as a well known griefer you will prolly have less fun to play.</description>
