    <item>
      <title>Re: How to Fix EQ PvP - Address the real issue</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=459#M459</link>
      <description>...so what could the devs do to improve PvP IMHO?&lt;br&gt;As I posted they should improve the rulesets/settings on the servers on the one hand (ok that would maybe need to include server moves or merging servers, dont know how likely that is since that needs manpower and thats costly). On the other hand they need to balance PvP to some degree. What I d like to see would be that no spell would be totally useless due to resists. There should always a minimum chance to be snared rooted dotted nuked etc. One shot kills are not really leading to interesting PvP but more to frustration. Should be looked into. Monks Warriors Rogues have a hard time PvPing - I think there is room for improvement here, making skills more valuable or adding special PvP skills. In general there won`t be 100% balanced PvP in any game, but every class should be effective vs a few other classes. Like the cleric being able to kill SKs necros easier due to resist modifiers lowered extremely, making root stun etc work well or Druids being Bard killers due to root snare sticking almost every time while warriors monks do extra damage vs Pallies and Shammies have less resists on Druids, etc. I think that it is less frustrating to have classes that are almost unkilleable or win button classes then everybody being vulnerable to a few other classes. Skill should always play a role, though.</description>
