      <title>Re: How to Fix EQ PvP - Address the real issue</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=457#M457</link>
      <description>Well, I really was no fan of PvP in general.&lt;br&gt;But what I love(d) are things like:&lt;br&gt;- smart "real" enemies and the thrill of crossing enemy territory (when VZ was brought up and I was a newbie running from RV to FP my invis dropped near the entrance to nektulous forrest - omg all the shouts in a language I did not understand! OMG half the zone is chasing meeeee! *sweat* Hop... Hop... Hop... ah finally the zoneline. Ah, wait  hope the humans there will be friendly to shorties!? )&lt;br&gt;- friendship, reputation really matter here. All the trouble on "blue" server, childish behaviour about loots and spawns. Not really possible on VZ if you want to belong to a top guild. Even left alone from the Developers we developed our own "code of honor" on the PvP servers like loot and scoot, dont attack when mob engaged, dont interfere raids when bossfights already started, dont train, etc. Sure, since there is no real power enforcing the rules besides the high level guilds (because of the game mechanics since harassing and getting harassed lead to no "phat lewtz") most of the rules will be only obeyed by highlevels and there are always debates and accusations, but in the end I think it works pretty well as long as all keep in mind that EQ is just a game and everybody can loose a fight or make a mistake...&lt;br&gt;- more options and a totally different "world"&lt;br&gt;- guild success and loot are really of value here not to forget the huge guildfights about bossmobs and zone control. Thats PvP how I like it - I suck at 1vs1 anyways ;)&lt;br&gt;For sure there are also downsides but I think that more bored players from "blue" servers would be surprised how interesting and different playing on a PvP server is. And the PvP community could benefit from the bigger attention they receive from the developers.</description>
