      <title>Re: How to Fix EQ PvP - Address the real issue</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=453#M453</link>
      <description>Honestly, I think the biggest issue is that there are different fractions of PvP players.&lt;br&gt;What I always liked about EQ PvP was that you had several choices in rulesets. But since the developers did not really communicate with the PvP community the setup of the servers was not well thought out and balanced. Since the game development after the PvP servers being no financial success purely shifted towards PvE now EQ PvP is even more broken. IMHO the first thing needed to balance PvP is to create a framework for the different PvP fractions via a server setup. Basically there are two groups of PvPers - the "hardcore" PvPers and the "bluebie" PvPers. Both fractions don't fit too well together since the hardcore PvPers want to have huge rewards for PvP victories while the blue ones PvP to have fun and for zones/mobs but want to have low penalties for PvP deaths. I'll leave it to the hardcore PvPers to write down their options about a good "hardcore" PvP server setup but will post some about a good setup for a "blue" PvP server. The "hardcore" PvPers probably know that only a "blue" PvP server has the chance to attract players from non PvP servers, increasing the playerbase and making SoE look more into PvP issues in general. The reason is simple: with no big penalties to PvP (coin loss only for example or expanded rez effects) harassing other players is not such a big issue here and thats what most non PvP players fear. They would be surprised that you can find a lot of mature people on PvP servers and friendship and reputation are of a real value here. Heck, there are even a bunch of IRL females playing on PvP servers - a fact that many of them prolly wont expect.&lt;br&gt;As far as I remember screenshots from RZ where Lighties and Darkies fought for Freeport excited the community and they demanded a PvP teams server - and got it, err ok them. IMHO the reason why it didnt work out as expected (still had incredible fun in my early newbie days after VZ was brought up) was that the setup wasnt arranged with the community. Thats also the reason why sullon flopped IMHO. &lt;br&gt;The Setup of PvP in DAoC isnt too bad for my taste, but for sure not balanced either. I personally would love kind of a Light vs Dark server, though. Since disrupting existing guilds is no option a guildwar server or the possibility of faction bringing you into the "team" you want to be in (Dark, Neutral, Light) could be a solution. And hey, imagine roleplaying a good Troll ;)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Or long story short: a lot of people fear to be harassed when playing on a PvP server.&lt;br&gt;The harder the punishment for PvP deaths the more effective harassing is possible.</description>
